<sn><md>### Course Learning Outcomes (CLOs)

* **CLO 1:** Understand the use of instruments for environmental analysis.
* **CLO 2:** Organize and manage industrial site visits and sample collections.
* **CLO 3:** Analyze and evaluate real-world environmental conditions.
* **CLO 4:** Design practical plans for pollution management and mitigation.</md></sn><sn><md>### Course Contents

| Topic                   | Details                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Field Visits**        | Sample collection from forest patches<br>wetlands<br>coastal areas<br>industrial sites                                                                                                                                                                                            |
| **Laboratory Analysis** | Water and wastewater testing (pH, EC, DO, BOD, COD, TDS, TSS)<br>air pollutant measurement (SO₂, CO₂)<br>biotreatment of industrial effluents<br>biogas production from organic waste<br>solid waste estimation and segregation<br>design of point-of-use water treatment systems |

